{
  "texts": [
    "Widely accessible Large Language Models show considerable early promise as educational tools (Choi et al, 2023, Henkel et al, 2024).",
    "One of the potential benefits generative AI brings to education is the ability to democratize the creation of new tools for learning and teaching.",
    "Since they can be \"programmed\" through prompts alone, instructors can more easily become tool creators, enabling transformative uses of technology that are directed by instructors for their specific classroom needs.",
    "In this paper we preview a future-focused approach to AI exercises for students that instructors can customize to suit their students, topics, and classrooms.",
    "Each of these exercises highlights a personalized learning activity -simulation, tutoring, mentoring, co-creation, etc."
  ]
}